  "texts": [
    "As artificial intelligence (AI) takes over increasingly many tasks, the question arises what should happen when AI systems start making decisions that have moral importance.",
    "Currently, the usage of AI systems is being proposed, or already in place, for tasks such as predicting re-offence risks of criminal defendants (Angwin et al., 2016), medical diagnosis (Sand et al., 2022), warfare (Umbrello et al., 2020), and traffic behaviour (Nyholm, 2018a, b) -just to give a few examples.",
    "When humans perform such tasks, they are expected to exercise moral competence in order to arrive at morally right decisions.",
    "The question is whether AI systems could exercise the same moral competence.",
    "If so, they may be able to autonomously perform such tasks in a 2008, Chap. 4; Anderson, 2011; Fossa, 2018)."
  ],
